# Drizzle Database

All database interactions must go through Drizzle ORM using this project's schema and query APIs.

## Key files

- Client: [src/db/index.ts](mdc:src/db/index.ts) — import `db` from here
- Schema: [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts) — table and relation definitions
- Migrations: [drizzle.config.ts](mdc:drizzle.config.ts) and `drizzle/` output

## Required patterns

- Import the shared client: `import { db } from "@/src/db"`
- Import tables from schema: `import { decksTable, cardsTable } from "@/src/db/schema"`
- Use Drizzle query builders (`select`, `insert`, `update`, `delete`) and operators from `drizzle-orm` (`eq`, `and`, `or`, etc.)

```typescript
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { db } from "@/src/db";
import { cardsTable, decksTable } from "@/src/db/schema";

const decks = await db.select().from(decksTable).where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

const [deck] = await db
  .insert(decksTable)
  .values({ userId, name: "Japanese" })
  .returning();
```

## User data isolation

Every query must scope data to the authenticated user. Never return or mutate another user's decks or cards.

- Get `userId` from Clerk auth (`currentUser()` / `auth()`), never from client input (request body, query params, headers)
- Set `decksTable.userId` on insert from the authenticated user's ID
- Always filter deck reads, updates, and deletes with `eq(decksTable.userId, userId)`
- Cards belong to decks via `deckId`; verify ownership through the parent deck's `userId` before reading or mutating cards

```typescript
import { and, eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/src/db";
import { cardsTable, decksTable } from "@/src/db/schema";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

// Decks: always filter by userId
const decks = await db
  .select()
  .from(decksTable)
  .where(eq(decksTable.userId, userId));

// Cards: join through decksTable to enforce ownership
const cards = await db
  .select({ id: cardsTable.id, front: cardsTable.front, back: cardsTable.back })
  .from(cardsTable)
  .innerJoin(decksTable, eq(cardsTable.deckId, decksTable.id))
  .where(and(eq(decksTable.id, deckId), eq(decksTable.userId, userId)));
```

## Schema changes

- Add or modify tables only in [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts)
- Generate migrations with `pnpm drizzle-kit generate`
- Apply migrations with `pnpm drizzle-kit migrate`

## Do not

- Use raw SQL (`sql` tagged templates, `db.execute`, direct `neon()` calls) outside [src/db/index.ts](mdc:src/db/index.ts)
- Introduce other ORMs (Prisma, Kysely, TypeORM, etc.)
- Create additional database clients or connection pools elsewhere
- Query tables not defined in the Drizzle schema
- Query `decksTable` without filtering on `userId`
- Access or modify cards without verifying the parent deck belongs to the current user
- Trust a client-supplied `userId` instead of the authenticated Clerk user ID
